      "clean_text": "At least two of our sister circuits have applied the “entire tort” rule as well. See O'Bryan v. Holy See, 556 F.3d 361, 382 (6th Cir.2009); Asociacion de Reclamantes v. United Mexican States , 735 F.2d 1517, 1525 (D.C.Cir.1984) (“Even if the [alleged tort] had the effect of retroactively rendering the prior acts on United States soil tortious, at the very least the entire tort would not have occurred here....”).”"
